# Proposal

## What will (likely) be the title of your project?

Minesweeper (something to do with minesweeper)

## In just a sentence or two, summarize your project. (E.g., "A website that lets you buy and sell stocks.")

A twist on minesweeper, a game where you are given a grid and need to pinpoint all tiles that have mines. Throughout solving the puzzle, you will earn abilities that will help you solve the grid more easily.

## In a paragraph or more, detail your project. What will your software do? What features will it have? How will it be executed?

Although I originally plan to create the code through python, I may change coding languages while I research and find that there is an easier and more efficient coding language to create a minesweeper game. I plan to create a code that creates a grid (size depending on difficulty and mines),
and randomly set mines around the grid. The code will also provide numbers that can help the user pinpoint where each mine is. In more difficult puzzles of minesweeper, there are times where the information given with the numbers is not enough to guarantee your guess, causing
a 50/50 chance of losing or winning. I found this frustrating at times, so I want to implement a code that gives you an ability at a chance each time you uncover a tile correctly. With the abilities, you will be able to more easily guess if there's a mine in each tile making
the game much easier. One of the abilities I have in mind is one where you are given immunity on your next guess. With this, you will be able to guess a 50/50 tile without worrying about losing, since if you do lose the 50/50, you won't die and you'll know which tile has the mine.
These are all rough ideas for now, but a general blueprint of what my final project will be.

## If planning to combine 1051's final project with another course's final project, with which other course? And which aspect(s) of your proposed project would relate to 1051, and which aspect(s) would relate to the other course?

I do not plan to combine this final project with another course.

## If planning to collaborate with 1 or 2 classmates for the final project, list their names, email addresses, and the names of their assigned TAs below.

